<p>Sixty-four South Korean nationals detained in Cambodia over alleged involvement in cyberscam operations were flown home on Saturday and placed under arrest as police opened a criminal investigation [scmp.com#1][dw.com#1][firstpost.com#1]. Seoul had sent a team to Cambodia on Wednesday to discuss the cases with local authorities, reflecting stepped-up coordination on cross-border fraud [scmp.com#1]. South Korea has also restricted travel to parts of Cambodia amid growing concerns about scam networks operating there [aljazeera.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/1kukmft27JORM0lMn42n_cTj_pFnc607sTCRJVkjFRrhCUXYeuXkYXbZpdkQzKJUNI-cEjKyb27nT1u0RfDrG6UKmnR4dR9zMFZuOVSCm1cUR-saGf83n0iDaFx_H-sdsEfeMmavH8pWT6pVtSYCq1IoP7YRNaUWOzTgOPEyQIiSDRG-weImmKCxfeWawdxqQ2G-cNeLEELdXYL-LvBtsJy8Jg8UFb90IBTTNAsFsSKhhC0av8w' alt='South Korean nationals repatriated from Cambodia amid a cyberscam investigation arrive in South Korea.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Chartered return: A police official said the group arrived at Incheon International Airport on a chartered flight [scmp.com#1].</li><li>Broader allegations: Investigators are probing suspected cyber fraud alongside human trafficking and other related crimes [firstpost.com#1].</li><li>Kidnapping reports: Seoul’s delegation went to Cambodia to address fake job schemes and scam centres alleged to have kidnapped dozens of South Koreans [scmp.com#1].</li><li>Revised numbers: Authorities had earlier indicated about 60 South Koreans were detained in Cambodia before 64 ultimately returned home [scmp.com#1].</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>South Korean police: Police placed the returnees under arrest on arrival and launched a criminal investigation into alleged links to cyberscam operations. (<a href='https://www.dw.com/en/scam-linked-south-koreans-held-in-cambodia-return-home-under-arrest/a-74408294'>DW</a>)</li><li>Government of South Korea: Officials dispatched a team to Cambodia to discuss fake job schemes and alleged kidnappings connected to scam centres targeting South Koreans. (<a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/asia/east-asia/article/3329487/64-south-koreans-scam-suspects-repatriated-cambodia-after-detention'>South China Morning Post</a>)</li><li>South Korean authorities (travel policy): Seoul restricted travel to parts of Cambodia in response to growing concerns about the country’s scam industry. (<a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/10/18/south-koreans-freed-from-cambodian-scam-centres-return-home-under-arrest'>Al Jazeera</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/10/18/south-koreans-freed-from-cambodian-scam-centres-return-home-under-arrest'>South Koreans freed from Cambodian scam centres return home under arrest</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.dw.com/en/scam-linked-south-koreans-held-in-cambodia-return-home-under-arrest/a-74408294'>Scam-linked South Koreans held in Cambodia return home under arrest</a> - dw.com</li><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/south-korea-arrests-64-nationals-repatriated-from-cambodia-over-online-fraud-operations-13943089.html'>South Korea arrests 64 nationals repatriated from Cambodia over online fraud operations</a> - firstpost.com</li><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/asia/east-asia/article/3329487/64-south-koreans-scam-suspects-repatriated-cambodia-after-detention'>64 South Korean cyber scam suspects repatriated from Cambodia</a> - scmp.com</li></ul>